{
  "stem": "151.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And apparently there was not room in the crematoria for these people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So they gassed them overnight, and then they were sitting there for about three days, until they were finally, slowly taken into the crematoria and disposed of.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so, a week later, I was selected from my camp, going into the other camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was then that I was separated from my sister, Clara.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And when Mengele pointed me to go to the other side, I tried to run back to my sister, because I knew she was weak.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "She was very skinny.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I knew she will not take a chance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I ran back to her, and Mangele caught me, and handed me to the kapo.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the kapo beat me brutally and pushed me back to the other side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we were separated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But we arranged to meet at the wires, through the wires, every morning at a certain place.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So that we can wave to each other, and tell each other that we are still alive, and we're still OK.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And on Yom Kippur, in 1944-- We were worried before Yom Kippur that something is going to happen, because the Nazis always had something in store for us during holidays or on Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I came to the wires, and my sister didn't show.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I thought maybe she was just upset because of the holiday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I thought maybe the following morning, and she didn't show then, either.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And when she didn't come the third day, I knew that something happened to her.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "After the war, I found out that there were bit selections in the C-lager, and that she was selected out to be killed that day.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, still, it was no different.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
